treatment and prevention of recurrence. As soon as the diagnosis is made, APA 
programs will become truly supportive care complementary of treatments, in other 
words non-pharmacological interventions (NPIs), with the aim of improving the 
quality of life of patients, improving their overall health, reducing side 
effects of treatment, potentiate the effects of certain treatments, and reduce 
the risk of recurrence. Research remains to be carried out notably on the 
survival, on the advanced cancers and on the integrative modelling of the 
mechanisms involved.

